      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ORDINARY ANGEL (5) finished runner-up at his last three outings and can get the job done at start five. Comes out of a solid rating contest after giving weight to Leovanni when a narrow second over 1400m at Tamworth. Will hold a forward position and worth noting Leovanni won in Highway grade at Randwick on July 11. Go close. MAGIC MERLIN (3) returned for his second campaign with a fast finishing second over 1280m at Muswellbrook. Looking for this trip now and can get off the mark quickly this prep. Main danger. REDALUCA GIRL (9) going better than her recent runs suggest. Closed strongly from an awkward gate to run fifth over 1450m at Quirindi in the soft (7) conditions. Adept in all going and can take a hand in the finish. SHARE OUR SECRET (6) modest effort first up last start, finishing fourth and beaten 2.75 lengths over 1280m at Muswellbrook. Fitter and can measure up with the right run.",
